[{"location":"#","page":"PottsGauge Documentation","title":"PottsGauge Documentation","text":"    CurrentModule = PottsGauge\n    DocTestSetup = quote\n    using PottsGauge\nend","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"PottsGauge Documentation","title":"PottsGauge Documentation","text":"    Modules = [PottsGauge]","category":"page"},{"location":"#PottsGauge.gauge-Union{Tuple{F}, Tuple{T}, Tuple{Array{F,4},Array{F,2},T}} where F<:Real where T<:PottsGauge.Gauge","page":"PottsGauge Documentation","title":"PottsGauge.gauge","text":"gauge(J,h,gauge::T)\n\nReturn the gauge-transform gauge of pair J,h. J,h are arrays of size q×q×N×N, q×N respectively. J should be symmetric: J[a,b,i,j] == J[b,a,j,i]. Allowed gauge are:  ZeroSumGauge,LatticeGas,WildType, ExternalGauge.\n\nUsage:\n\ngauge(J,h,ZeroSumGauge())\ngauge(J,h,Wildtype(x0))\ngauge(J,h,ExternalGauge(U,V,C))\n\nwhere:\n\n* For `WildType` `x0` is a `Vector{Int}` of size `N` whose values are in the interval `1,…,q`\n\n* For `ExternalGauge`, `U`,`V` are `q×N×N` arrays, and C is vector of length `N`.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#PottsGauge.Energy-Tuple{Any,Any,Any}","page":"PottsGauge Documentation","title":"PottsGauge.Energy","text":"function Energy(J,h,x)\n\nCompute the energy with parameters J::Array{T,4},h::Array{T,2} of a  configuration x::Array{Int,1} of integer elements. x[i] ∈ 1:q where q is the number of letters (e.g. q=21 in MSA with gaps);\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#PottsGauge.testgauge-NTuple{4,Any}","page":"PottsGauge Documentation","title":"PottsGauge.testgauge","text":"function testgauge(J1,h1,J2,h2; nsample::Integer)\n\nTest if parameters J1,h1 and J2,h2 are gauge related; Return mean and std of the energy difference induced by the two set of parameters J1,h1 and J2,h2 of nsample random configurations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#PottsGauge-Documentation-1","page":"PottsGauge Documentation","title":"PottsGauge Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"PottsGauge Documentation","title":"PottsGauge Documentation","text":"    gauge","category":"page"},{"location":"#PottsGauge.gauge","page":"PottsGauge Documentation","title":"PottsGauge.gauge","text":"gauge(J,h,gauge::T)\n\nReturn the gauge-transform gauge of pair J,h. J,h are arrays of size q×q×N×N, q×N respectively. J should be symmetric: J[a,b,i,j] == J[b,a,j,i]. Allowed gauge are:  ZeroSumGauge,LatticeGas,WildType, ExternalGauge.\n\nUsage:\n\ngauge(J,h,ZeroSumGauge())\ngauge(J,h,Wildtype(x0))\ngauge(J,h,ExternalGauge(U,V,C))\n\nwhere:\n\n* For `WildType` `x0` is a `Vector{Int}` of size `N` whose values are in the interval `1,…,q`\n\n* For `ExternalGauge`, `U`,`V` are `q×N×N` arrays, and C is vector of length `N`.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
